{"ts": "2026-06-07T22:29:43.918116+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: f2eba89c3234fe5e1e08e09360624b73ba6212ee)", "id": "lc_82589632-579e-49f5-8da2-5b98b3bd7b02"}, {"type": "text", "text": "const tokens = {\n  admin: {\n    token: 'admin-token',\n  },\n  editor: {\n    token: 'editor-token',\n  },\n}\n\nconst users = {\n  'admin-token': {\n    roles: ['admin'],\n    introduction: 'I am a super administrator',\n    avatar:\n      'https://wpimg.wallstcn.com/f778738c-e4f8-4870-b634-56703b4acafe.gif',\n    name: 'Super Admin',\n  },\n  'editor-token': {\n    roles: ['editor'],\n    introduction: 'I am an editor',\n    avatar:\n      'https://wpimg.wallstcn.com/f778738c-e4f8-4870-b634-56703b4acafe.gif',\n    name: 'Normal Editor',\n  },\n}\n\nmodule.exports = [\n  // user login\n  {\n    url: '/vue-admin-template/user/login',\n    type: 'post',\n    response: (config) => {\n      const { username } = config.body\n      const token = tokens[username]\n\n      // mock error\n      if (!token) {\n        return {\n          code: 60204,\n          message: 'Account and password are incorrect.',\n        }\n      }\n\n      return {\n        code: 20000,\n        data: token,\n      }\n    },\n  },\n\n  // get user info\n  {\n    url: '/vue-admin-template/user/info.*',\n    type: 'get',\n    response: (config) => {\n      const { token } = config.query\n      const info = users[token]\n\n      // mock error\n      if (!info) {\n        return {\n          code: 50008,\n          message: 'Login failed, unable to get user details.',\n        }\n      }\n\n      return {\n        code: 20000,\n        data: info,\n      }\n    },\n  },\n\n  // user logout\n  {\n    url: '/vue-admin-template/user/logout',\n    type: 'post',\n    response: () => {\n      return {\n        code: 20000,\n        data: 'success',\n      }\n    },\n  },\n]\n", "id": "lc_d6297767-d183-43ac-9c05-12b39ca6f473"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "db5ca9ee-4927-45a5-9b84-e446358a4302", "tool_call_id": "call_1b23140387494c90809be389", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-07T22:29:51.702486+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Here's the full picture:\n\n---\n\n## How the API base path switches between environments\n\nThe template uses **Vue CLI's environment-file convention** to set the base API path at build/dev time:\n\n| File | `ENV` value | `VUE_APP_BASE_API` |\n|---|---|---|\n| `.env.development` | `development` | `/dev-api` |\n| `.env.staging` | `staging` | `/stage-api` |\n| `.env.production` | `production` | `/prod-api` |\n\nVue CLI automatically loads the `.env.*` file matching the current `--mode` flag (e.g. `npm run dev` loads `.env.development`, `npm run build` loads `.env.production`). The `VUE_APP_BASE_API` variable is then exposed to all client-side code via `process.env.VUE_APP_BASE_API`, where an HTTP client (e.g. Axios) typically uses it as the `baseURL`.\n\nAdditionally, `vue.config.js` uses the `isDev` flag (`process.env.NODE_ENV === 'development'`) to toggle:\n- **`publicPath`**: `'/'` in development vs. `'/vue3-admin-template/'` in production.\n- **`lintOnSave`**: enabled only in development.\n- **CSS source maps**: enabled only in development.\n- **Code-splitting / chunk optimizations**: applied only when `NODE_ENV !== 'development'`.\n\nIn dev mode, `vue.config.js` also wires in a **mock server** (`devServer.before: require('./mock/mock-server.js')`), which intercepts API requests before they leave the dev server.\n\n---\n\n## Mock login usernames and their tokens\n\nDefined in **`mock/user.js`**, the `tokens` map:\n\n| Username | Token |\n|---|---|\n| `admin` | `admin-token` |\n| `editor` | `editor-token` |\n\nThe corresponding user profiles (returned by the `/vue-admin-template/user/info` endpoint when looked up by token) are:\n\n| Token | Roles | Display Name |\n|---|---|---|\n| `admin-token` | `['admin']` | **Super Admin** |\n| `editor-token` | `['editor']` | **Normal Editor** |\n\nSo when you POST to the mock login endpoint with `{ \"username\": \"admin\" }`, you get back `token: \"admin-token\"`; with `{ \"username\": \"editor\" }`, you get `token: \"editor-token\"`. Any other username returns a **60204** error (\"Account and password are incorrect\").", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 551, "prompt_tokens": 8367, "total_tokens": 8918, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 13, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 7744, "cache_write_tokens": 0, "video_tokens": 0}, "cost": 0, "is_byok": true, "cost_details": {"upstream_inference_cost": 0.0002631832, "upstream_inference_prompt_cost": 0.0001089032, "upstream_inference_completions_cost": 0.00015428}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-20260422", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "gen-1780871384-YTGsLYzcH1m4VqQSlEjH", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea434-cb6f-7783-909b-e97ff2388d75-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 8367, "output_tokens": 551, "total_tokens": 8918, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 7744}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 13}}}}]}}}
